## .rule = forbid-term-normalize

### .what
term `normalize` forbidden ‚Äî overloaded and vague

### .scope
- code: variable names, function names, comments
- files: filenames, directory names
- docs: markdown, briefs, prompts
- comms: commit messages, pr descriptions

### .why
- `normalize` causes semantic diffusion
- makes communication unclear
- forces reader to guess definition
- hides actual transformation

### .purposes
term used for 8+ purposes:

| purpose       | definition                          | alternative          |
| ------------- | ----------------------------------- | -------------------- |
| format        | convert to standard format          | `asE164`             |
| canonical     | reduce for comparison               | `asSha256`           |
| sanitize      | clean untrusted input               | `asTrimmed`          |
| scale         | adjust numeric range                | `asUnitVector`       |
| case          | convert letter case                 | `asLowercase`        |
| encode        | convert character form              | `asNfc`              |
| resolve       | resolve to absolute                 | `asAbsolute`         |
| collapse      | reduce redundancy                   | `asCollapsed`        |

### .enforcement
use of `normalize` = blocker

### .pattern: asX
recommended: `asX` pattern
- describes target form
- self-documenting: e.g., `asE164`
- composable: `input.asTrimmed().asLowercase()`
- reads naturally: "give value as X"

### .common usecases

| üëé vague              | üëç precise          | what it does                   |
| -------------------- | ------------------ | ------------------------------ |
| `normalizePhone`     | `asE164`           | format to E.164 standard       |
| `normalizeEmail`     | `asLowercase`      | lowercase email                |
| `normalizeString`    | `asTrimmed`        | remove initial/final space     |
| `normalizePath`      | `asAbsolute`       | resolve to absolute path       |
| `normalizeUrl`       | `asCanonical`      | dedupe slashes, sort params    |
| `normalizeDate`      | `asIso8601`        | format to ISO 8601             |
| `normalizeTimestamp` | `asUtc`            | convert to UTC                 |
| `normalizeCase`      | `asCamelCase`      | convert to camelCase           |
| `normalizeSlug`      | `asKebabCase`      | convert to kebab-case          |
| `normalizeJson`      | `asSorted`         | sort keys                      |
| `normalizeUnicode`   | `asNfc`            | unicode form C                 |
| `normalizeWhitespace`| `asCollapsed`      | collapse multiple spaces       |
| `normalizeNumber`    | `asScaled`         | scale to range (e.g., 0-1)     |

### .examples

**üëé bad**
```ts
const asE164 = (phone: string) => { ... };
const emailLowercased = asLowercase(email);
const data = asTrimmed(rawData);

// as methods
const phone = input.phone.asE164();
const email = input.email.asLowercase();
```

### .note
when `asX` vague, get specific:

| üëé vague      | üëç specific          |
| ------------- | -------------------- |
| `asFormatted` | `asE164`             |
| `asCleaned`   | `asTrimmed`          |
| `asStandard`  | `asIso8601`          |

### .pattern: as${DomainObject}
use domain object:
```ts
// target forms
const priceStandard = asIsoPrice(input);
const phoneStandard = asPhoneE164(input);

const // cast to object
const customer = asCustomer(rawData);
```

domain object variants:
```ts
// IsoPrice representations
const forDisplay = asIsoPriceHuman(price);   // "$1,234.56"
const forSpeech = asIsoPriceWords(price);    // "one thousand..."
const forStorage = asIsoPriceShape(price);   // { amount: 123456, ... }
```

